cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on securing wireless sensor networks against DoS attacks using RSA cryptography algorithm and interlock protocol. This falls under the scope of cs.CR.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their communication protocols. This falls under the scope of cs.NI.
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a clustering approach based on energy and distance to select the proper cluster head. This falls under the scope of cs.DS.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper mentions the Abnormal Sensor Detection Accuracy (ASDA-RSA) method, which could potentially involve machine learning techniques. This falls under the scope of cs.LG.
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a method to enhance security in WSNs, which involves the use of an authentication method. This falls under the scope of cs.SE.
